      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\AFJ_Cardiff_All_Websites\\Legal_Framework_AFJ_MERCH_WHATNOT.txt</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ﻿=== Merch / Whatnot / E-commerce mentions from 'Legal Framework for AFJ Cardiff.json' ===\n2: \n3: Source: C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\StefaniaOkereke\\Legal Framework for AFJ Cardiff.json\n4: \n5: \n6: \n7: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T13:12:34.019Z\"     }, { L131:       \"text\": \"Based on the provided context, the contract stack for AFJ Cardiff consists of eight distinct documents spanning six key relationships. To ensure the newly incorporated entity (**AFJ Cardiff Ltd**) is legally secure and compliant with the Arts Council of Wales (ACW) and HMRC requirements, these agreements must be structured properly under English and Welsh law.\\n\\nBelow is a detailed legal and historical analysis of the pre-incorporation sequence, followed by an audit of each required document, their original legal names, their historical context, their mapping to **SeedLegals** templates, and direct corroborating quotes from UK statutes and legal authorities.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Part 1: Pre-Incorporation Legal Framework (*Mise en Place*)\\n\\nBefore any contracts are signed, three critical legal issues must be resolved. Sourcing templates from official places (such as GOV.UK, Seedsummit, or the Open Legal Library) and adapting them with tracked changes in Microsoft Word is a legally sound, non-reserved activity under the **Legal Services Act 2007**.\\n\\n### 1. The Pre-Incorporation Assignee Nullity\\nCurrently, the drafts name \\\"AFJ Cardiff\\\" as the contracting party. Because AFJ Cardiff is currently an unincorporated association, it lacks a distinct legal personality under English law. It cannot own property, hold copyright, or be a party to a contract. \\n\\n*   **Verbatim Statute (Companies Act 2006, Section 51(1)):**\\n    \\u003e *\\\"A contract that purports to be made by or on behalf of a company at a time when the company has not been formed has effect, subject to any agreement to the contrary, as one made with the person purporting to act for the company or as agent for it, and he is personally liable on the contract accordingly.\\\"*\\n*   **The Precedent (*Kelner v Baxter* (1866)):**\\n    \\u003e *\\\"As there was no company in existence at the time [of signing], the contract would be wholly inoper... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n8: \n9: […]         \"text\": \"PA 1988 |\\n| **HomeBros / Miss Lulu** | Collaboration\"       }, { L409:         \"text\": \" and Workshop Agreement | **Collaboration / Partnership Agreement** | Partnership Act 1890 (Avoiding implied partnership) |\\n| **And\"       }, {         \"text\": \"ie Kobbie** (Tech Lead) | Contract for Services (Independent Contractor) | **Advisor Agreement / Consultancy Agreement** | s.3\" […]\n10: \n11: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T13:45:47.478Z\"     }, { L1553:       \"text\": \"### 1. \\\"Making Dez’s IP assignment fully binding\\\" — What this means in practice\\n\\nTo say the assignment is \\\"fully binding\\\" means that once the document is signed, **Dez\\u0027s legal ownership of the code, CMS, and database is permanently extinguished** and transferred entirely to AFJ Cardiff [bf4f4336-e5de-48f2-8c1d-231a1e5b9a21, 99f9eda0-a6ff-4937-8c60-5c7f7b6c12a1]. \\n\\nHere is the difference between a \\\"fully binding\\\" assignment and a defective one:\\n\\n*   **If it IS fully binding:** AFJ Cardiff Ltd owns the digital infrastructure. Plamedi can host it, edit it, hire another developer to change it, or license it commercially [bf4f4336-e5de-48f2-8c1d-231a1e5b9a21]. If Dez later has a disagreement with the group, he cannot legally demand that AFJ stop using the site, he cannot take the site down, and he cannot sue for copyright infringement. It becomes a clean asset on AFJ\\u0027s balance sheet that funders (like ACW) can safely rely on [bf4f4336-e5de-48f2-8c1d-231a1e5b9a21, eadf5d3e-9136-4f94-9160-9a6fc2fc8e9a].\\n*   **If it is NOT fully binding:** Dez remains the sole legal owner of the copyright in the code [bf4f4336-e5de-48f2-8c1d-231a1e5b9a21]. He has merely granted AFJ an informal, implied verbal licence to use it. Because that licence is informal and unpaid, Dez can legally revoke it at any time. He could send a cease-and-desist letter, demand that AFJ take down the website, or lock them out of the server. For a funding body or future investor, this is a fatal flaw; they will not award grants to an organization that does not legally own its own website and data platform [eadf5d3e-9136-4f94-9160-9a6fc2fc8e9a].\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. \\\"Without any consideration\\\" — What this means\\n\\nIn English contract law, \\\"consideration\\\" is the legal term for **the exchange of value** — the price paid by one party for the promise of the other [1.4.8, 2.2.4]. It is the \\\"quid pro quo\\\" (somethi... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n12: \n13: […]         \"text\": \" prejudicial to the honor or reputation of the author.\\n*   **The Risk:** Every time AFJ crops his 4K footage for a vertical\"       }, { L1644:         \"text\": \" TikTok clip, cuts a 2-hour workshop down to a 30-second promo, or overlays someone else\\u0027s music,\"       }, {         \"text\": \" David could legally claim AFJ is \\\"mutilating\\\" his artistic work and sue for infringement of his moral rights\" […]\n14: \n15: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T13:52:33.376Z\"     }, { L1968:       \"text\": \"No, David (David Mac) is **not** the videographer you are currently chasing. David is your highly trusted, long-term videographer who has shot almost the entirety of AFJ Cardiff\\u0027s historical catalogue. He is incredibly reliable, offers a 50% discount, and is excellent at capturing the AFJ \\\"DNA\\\" with minimal revisions.\\n\\nThe videographer you are currently **chasing** is an **unnamed \\\"fill-in\\\" (temporary) videographer** who was brought in to cover a previous workshop. This temporary shooter has caused a **1-month delay** on delivering the promotional footage, which has directly stalled Sonia\\u0027s marketing push for your subsequent classes [Accuracy_verification.json]. \\n\\n---\\n\\n### Who else has been used or hired?\\n\\nApart from David and the delayed fill-in shooter, there are three other media creators and filmmakers in the AFJ Cardiff ecosystem:\\n\\n#### 1. Onismo Muhlanga (representing *Urban Stamp*)\\n*   **The Role:** He is the multidisciplinary filmmaker and Artistic Director of **Urban Stamp** (based in Newport). \\n*   **The Work:** Onismo is the lead filmmaker secured to shoot and document the major **\\\"Movement is Memory and Storytelling\\\"** R\\u0026D documentary project [Accuracy_verification.json, d8252753-69f5-4a13-bc41-69daee74a505]. Plamedi needs his signed contract in place before the July 28 funding decision so his team can begin storyboarding immediately if the grant is approved [Accuracy_verification.json, d8252753-69f5-4a13-bc41-69daee74a505].\\n\\n#### 2. Wolfget Media\\n*   **The Role:** A Welsh content creation and corporate videography agency based in South Wales.\\n*   **The Work:** They served as your \\\"videography plug\\\" in your early days, shooting some of AFJ\\u0027s first-ever major promotional videos, such as the highlight reel for your Angolan Afrohouse workshop in 2022.\\n\\n#### 3. Sam\\n*   **The Role:** A filmmaker collaborator [99f9eda0-a6ff-4937-8c60... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n16: \n17: […]         \"text\": \" Wales.\\n*   **The Work:** They served as your \\\"videography plug\\\" in your early days\"       }, { L2078:         \"text\": \", shooting some of AFJ\\u0027s first-ever major promotional videos, such as the highlight reel for your Angolan Afrohouse workshop in\"       }, {         \"text\": \" 2022.\\n\\n#### 3. Sam\\n*   **The Role\" […]\n18: \n19: […]         \"text\": \" [99f9eda0-a6ff-4937-8c60-5c7f7b6c12a1].\\n\\n### Summary of the Action Plan:\\nYou are chasing the **temporary fill-in** to get\"       }, { L2090:         \"text\": \" the delayed workshop video so Sonia can edit it and post it on socials [Accuracy_verification.json]. Meanwhile, you are preparing a\"       }, {         \"text\": \" **Deed of Assignment** for **David** to secure ownership of the years of archive footage he holds under UK copyright\" […]\n20: \n21: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T14:04:01.109Z\"     }, { L2657:       \"text\": \" The Case Law: Vetta v London Dreams Motion Pictures Ltd [2008]\\nThis is the landmark Employment Tribunal case that proved how this law is enforced against private companies.\\nThe Facts: A private, commercial film production company hired an assistant, Ms. Vetta, to work in their art department. She agreed to work \\\"for free\\\" (as a volunteer/intern) to gain experience and screen credits, with only her basic out-of-pocket expenses reimbursed[8][9].\\nThe Ruling: The Tribunal ruled that because the employer was a private, commercial business, it was legally impossible for them to use the \\\"voluntary worker\\\" exemption[8]. Because she was personally performing services for the business, she was legally classified as a \\\"worker\\\" under the Act and was awarded full back-pay at the National Minimum Wage for every hour she had worked.\\nThe Legal Principle: A private business cannot bypass the minimum wage by having a worker sign an agreement stating they are a \\\"volunteer\\\" or that they agree to work \\\"for free\\\"[5][7]. The moment there is an obligation to personally perform work for a for-profit commercial entity, the statutory right to the National Minimum Wage is automatically triggered[9][10].\\n\\ndoes insrunace cover plamedi??\\n\\nFinal Team Agreements – Unlocking Marketing, Site(s) Development (Merch \\u0026 Classroom), Proportional Governance Consolidation\\nFrom:\\tandiekobbietks@outlook.com (andiekobbietks@outlook.com)\\nTo:\\tplamediakiso@hotmail.com\\nCc:\\tafjcardiff@gmail.com\\nDate:\\tThursday, 7 May 2026 at 07:17 BST\\n\\nHi Plam,\\n\\nThank you for your patience while I finished these. I’m sending over the\\nfinalised agreement packs for Sonia and Dez first so we can get them moving and\\n\\\"unlocked\\\" immediately.\\n\\nI’ve prioritised these two ahead of the the necessary final technical setup for the\\nMerch Shop and AFJ Classroom ready to hand over. To protect the business and\\nyour data, Dez m... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n22: \n23: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T14:21:43.987Z\"     }, { L3251:       \"text\": \"**Defining the Objective**\\n\\nI\\u0027m now zeroing in on the core of the user\\u0027s need. I\\u0027m focusing on parsing the question to define the actionable requirements. My immediate focus is formulating a concise response outlining what \\\"Plamedi\\\" needs to do. The goal is to provide a clear and direct answer.\\n\\n\\n**Summarizing Actionable Steps**\\n\\nI\\u0027m now consolidating the actionable items for Plamedi, derived from reviewing all pre-incorporation steps, legal considerations, contracts, and funding aspects. I\\u0027ve pinpointed the most immediate action: contacting Stiwdio/Capital Law via email or phone to schedule a free consultation, explicitly mentioning Andie\\u0027s role. My focus is delivering a clear, concise outline of what needs to be done.\\n\\n\\n**Outlining Required Steps**\\n\\nI\\u0027ve got three new actionable steps clearly outlined. First, I see the need to check the Creative Steps grant budget for freelancer costs. If they are not included, I need to request a written variation before spending any funds. Then, there is a compulsory Stiwdio workshop on financing to attend. Lastly, the contracting party name must be updated before signing anything.\\n\\n\\n\",       \"role\": \"model\",       \"tokenCount\": 1077, […]\n24: \n25: […]         \"thought\": true       }, { L3263:         \"text\": \"**Outlining Required Steps**\\n\\nI\\u0027ve got three new actionable steps clearly outlined. First, I see the need to check the Creative Steps grant budget for freelancer costs. If they are not included, I need to request a written variation before spending any funds. Then, there is a compulsory Stiwdio workshop on financing to attend. Lastly, the contracting party name must be updated before signing anything.\\n\\n\\n\",         \"thought\": true       }], […]\n26: \n27: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T14:21:43.988Z\"     }, { L3268:       \"text\": \"Based on our comprehensive review of AFJ Cardiff\\u0027s legal, financial, and funding structures, Plamedi has **six direct actions** she needs to take. \\n\\nTo prevent her from being overwhelmed, these are stripped of legal jargon and sequenced in order of immediate priority:\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 1. Send the Stiwdio Referral Email (Today)\\nPlamedi must request the free Capital Law contract review. Because you cannot legally represent her without a written agreement, **she** must send the email herself [019ef43d-d20b-7e5b-816f-bac15bf20104].\\n*   **What she needs to do:** Email `stiwdio@southwales.ac.uk` (or call `029 2047 0353`) [019ef454-bf15-7872-8f8c-14fa562fddf8].\\n*   **What she must include:** She must explicitly state: *“My technical advisor, Andie Kobbie, will be joining me for the consultation.”* This single sentence gives you the formal standing to attend the Capital Law meeting and represent her technical interests [019ef43d-d20b-7e5b-816f-bac15bf20104].\\n\\n### 2. Check her Creative Steps Grant Budget (Today)\\nBefore you can invoice her for technical work, she must verify if the grant can legally pay you [019ef427-400e-7e72-bf9c-ca4c48c25509].\\n*   **What she needs to do:** Pull up her original *Creative Steps for Individuals* application and grant offer letter [019ef427-400e-7e72-bf9c-ca4c48c25509].\\n*   **The check:** Look at the approved budget lines. Is there a line for \\\"technical, digital, or website freelancer costs\\\"? [019ef427-400e-7e72-bf9c-ca4c48c25509]\\n*   **If YES:** You can draft your Technical Lead agreement and invoice once the work is completed [019ef427-400e-7e72-bf9c-ca4c48c25509].\\n*   **If NO:** She must contact her ACW Relationship Manager to request a written budget variation *before* any grant money is spent on your fees [019ef427-400e-7e72-bf9c-ca4c48c25509].\\n\\n### 3. Log on to the Compulsory Stiwdio Workshop (Thursday)\\nTo keep her free Stiwdio co-working... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n28: \n29: […]         \"text\": \" [019ef427-400e-7e72-bf9c-ca4c48c25509].\\n\\n### 3.\"       }, { L3317:         \"text\": \" Log on to the Compulsory Stiwdio Workshop (Thursday)\\nTo keep her free Stiwdio co\"       }, {         \"text\": \"-working and mentoring perks active, she must satisfy the attendance requirement\" […]\n30: \n31: […]         \"text\": \" [019ef408-84a9-79fe-a4a9-f34c4213d473].\\n*   \"       }, { L3323:         \"text\": \"**What she needs to do:** Log on to the Zoom workshop on *Financing, Grants, and Budgeting* this Thursday from 10:\"       }, {         \"text\": \"00 AM to 1:00 PM\" […]\n32: \n33: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T14:53:46.749Z\"     }, { L4714:       \"text\": \"**Analyzing the User\\u0027s Intent**\\n\\nI\\u0027m currently focused on fully grasping the user\\u0027s implicit request within the provided context. I\\u0027ve noted they desire a .md version of Sonia\\u0027s SOP, taking recent chats into account. I\\u0027m prioritizing the integration of the newly supplied WhatsApp file, aiming to understand how it influences the final SOP output.\\n\\n\\n**Extracting Recent Chat Data**\\n\\nI\\u0027m now diving deep into the provided chat log (`_chat 17.txt`) to extract the \\\"recent happenings\\\" and specifics about Sonia\\u0027s role between April 2025 and June 2026. My goal is to extract relevant operational details. I am paying close attention to the timeline. I\\u0027ll need to summarize all the crucial interactions to construct Sonia\\u0027s SOP in Markdown format.\\n\\n\\n**Recalling Sonia\\u0027s Contributions**\\n\\nI\\u0027m processing Sonia\\u0027s impact using the new data. I see she joined in April 2026 as interim Marketer. I\\u0027m focusing on the \\\"Videographer Crisis\\\" and Sonia\\u0027s swift response to retrieve the Amapiano workshop footage. I\\u0027m considering how this incident demonstrates her problem-solving abilities within the team.\\n\\n\\n**Detailing Sonia\\u0027s Achievements**\\n\\nI\\u0027m now focusing on Sonia\\u0027s contributions. I have gathered details about the Eventbrite banner and Instagram story posters that Sonia designed. I\\u0027ve also extracted information about her editing of the Amapiano promotional video in CapCut, including the WCAG 2.3.1 Photosensitive Epilepsy flash warning and the AFJ logo. I\\u0027ve also noted that Sonia built the temporary \\\"Content Output Tracker\\\" in Google Sheets and created the Trello board. I am organizing these findings methodically.\\n\\n\\n**Documenting Sonia\\u0027s Calendar**\\n\\nI\\u0027m currently documenting Sonia\\u0027s work schedule during April-June 2026. This includes details on YouTube Shorts content an... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n34: \n35: […]         \"thought\": true       }, { L4726:         \"text\": \"**Recalling Sonia\\u0027s Contributions**\\n\\nI\\u0027m processing Sonia\\u0027s impact using the new data. I see she joined in April 2026 as interim Marketer. I\\u0027m focusing on the \\\"Videographer Crisis\\\" and Sonia\\u0027s swift response to retrieve the Amapiano workshop footage. I\\u0027m considering how this incident demonstrates her problem-solving abilities within the team.\\n\\n\\n\",         \"thought\": true       }, { […]\n36: \n37: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T14:53:46.751Z\"     }, { L4743:       \"text\": \"# STANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURE (SOP)\\n**Document Ref:** AFJ-SOP-MKT-001  \\n**Version:** 2.0 (Post-Consolidation)  \\n**Effective Date:** 23 June 2026  \\n**Owner:** Technical Lead \\u0026 Governance Advisor (Andie Kobbie)  \\n**Approved by:** Founder \\u0026 Creative Director (Plamedi Santima-Akiso)  \\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. Document Overview \\u0026 Legal Status\\n\\n### 1.1 Statement of Purpose\\nThis Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) formalizes the operational workflows, marketing responsibilities, and compliance standards for the role of **Interim Marketer \\u0026 Social Media Lead** (currently held by Sonia Fellah) [9316d57e-4e50-46b8-9ab2-3e374337ff3c]. It acts as an operational addendum linked to the master **Consultancy Agreement (v2)**, making these guidelines contractually binding upon electronic signature [Final Team Agreements email].\\n\\n### 1.2 Self-Employed Status \\u0026 Legal Boundaries\\nUnder English and Welsh law, the Marketer is engaged strictly as an **independent, self-employed contractor (consultant)** under a contract *for* services, not an employee under a contract *of* service (*Ready Mixed Concrete [1968]*) [1.4.1]. To maintain these boundaries and protect the organization from National Minimum Wage (NMW) and employer tax liabilities, the following principles apply:\\n*   **No Mutuality of Obligation:** The Marketer is not guaranteed a set number of hours and is free to accept or decline projects.\\n*   **Operational Autonomy:** The Marketer has absolute control over when, where, and how she performs her marketing work, utilizing her own personal equipment (Bring Your Own Device - BYOD) [1.1.7].\\n*   **Right of Substitution:** The Marketer has the right to appoint a qualified substitute to deliver the marketing tasks if she is unavailable.\\n\\n### 1.3 Services-in-Kind (Barter) Valuation\\nNo cash is exchanged for these services [9316d57e-4e50-46b8-9ab2-3e374337ff3c]. The considerat... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n38: \n39: […]         \"text\": \" established in *Chappell \\u0026 Co Ltd v Nestle Co Ltd [1960]*, where Sonia\\u0027s marketing services are traded for\"       }, { L4788:         \"text\": \" Plamedi’s professional dance training and workshop access\"       }, {         \"text\": \" [1, 9316d57e-4e50-46b8-9ab2-3e374337ff3c]. \\n*   \" […]\n40: \n41: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T14:55:43.982Z\"     }, { L4998:       \"text\": \"In practical terms, migrating to the **Linagora stack** and utilizing the **LinShare MCP** means transitioning AFJ Cardiff from fragmented, US-hosted, third-party software (like Google Drive, DocuSign, and Fathom) to a **single, 100% self-hosted, sovereign digital office** running on your own infrastructure (**AKCloud**) [019ef485-52a2-7c6d-8796-73365b2d8d71, 019ef48d-8eef-7159-ae9d-2b041e2a0bd9].\\n\\nHere is exactly what those two components are and how they work together:\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 1. What is LinShare?\\n**LinShare** is Linagora’s open-source, highly secure file-sharing and storage platform. It is a private, GDPR-compliant alternative to Dropbox, Google Drive, or WeTransfer [019ef485-52a2-7c6d-8796-73365b2d8d71]. Instead of storing your contract PDFs and dance video archives on Google\\u0027s servers, they are stored securely on your own cloud instance [019ef485-52a2-7c6d-8796-73365b2d8d71].\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. What is MCP?\\n**MCP** stands for **Model Context Protocol** [019ef485-52a2-7c6d-8796-73365b2d8d71]. It is an open standard developed to securely connect AI models (like Claude) to external data sources, files, and local tools [019ef485-52a2-7c6d-8796-73365b2d8d71].\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. What does \\\"LinShare MCP\\\" mean for AFJ Cardiff?\\n\\nOn 12 June 2026, Linagora launched a **LinShare MCP server** [019ef485-52a2-7c6d-8796-73365b2d8d71]. This is the technological bridge that allows your self-hosted AI assistant to directly interact with your secure business files on LinShare [019ef485-52a2-7c6d-8796-73365b2d8d71]. \\n\\nOnce this is deployed on your AKCloud, it enables the following automated workflows [e8e9804c-a859-4727-9613-f4ff9e7597b8, 019ef485-52a2-7c6d-8796-73365b2d8d71]:\\n\\n*   **One-Click Contract Generation \\u0026 Delivery:** Instead of manually editing Word files and copying them into DocuSign, you can instruct the AI inside your chat workspace: *“Draft a new Statement of Wor... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n42: \n43: […]         \"text\": \" Asset Archiving:** You can ask the AI: *â€œGo through our raw video archive in Twake Drive/LinShare, read\"       }, { L5057:         \"text\": \" the metadata, and group all the 2025 Amapiano workshop footage into a single folder for Sonia to\"       }, {         \"text\": \" access.â€* \\n\\n**Summary:**  \\nIt means you are building a **private, automated administrative engine** for Pl\" […]\n44: \n45: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T15:24:47.718Z\"     }, { L6335:       \"text\": \"Sonia executes this legal certification through a simple, standardized administrative document called a **Certificate of Data Deletion** (or *Certificate of Data Destruction/Erasure*) [Final Team Agreements email]. \\n\\nShe does not need to visit a solicitor or a notary; she simply signs the document electronically [019ef48d-8eef-7159-ae9d-2b041e2a0bd9]. Once signed, the document is archived as a permanent, audit-proof record to satisfy the ICO and protect Plamedi from liability [e6e5a729-0d40-42aa-b176-1e8841cc5242, 019ef48d-8eef-7159-ae9d-2b041e2a0bd9].\\n\\nHere is exactly how the document is structured, how it is written, and how the workflow operates:\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 1. The Template: What the Certificate actually says\\n\\nTo be legally robust under English contract law and UK GDPR, you (Andie) will prepare a simple, one-page template containing this exact verbatim language [Final Team Agreements email]:\\n\\n\\u003e **AFJ CARDYFF — CERTIFICATE OF DATA DELETION**\\n\\u003e \\n\\u003e **Date of Eradication:** `[Insert Date]`  \\n\\u003e **Consultant:** Sonia Fellah (Self-Employed Consultant)  \\n\\u003e **Client:** Plamedi Santima-Akiso trading as AFJ Cardiff [9316d57e-4e50-46b8-9ab2-3e374337ff3c]  \\n\\u003e \\n\\u003e I, Sonia Fellah, hereby certify that in accordance with Clause `[X]` of the Data Processing Agreement (DPA) dated `[Date of original contract]` [Final Team Agreements email]:\\n\\u003e \\n\\u003e 1.  All personal data, student registration details, email databases, proprietary marketing graphics, and raw video footage belonging to AFJ Cardiff have been permanently deleted and erased from all personal devices, local hard drives, and cloud storage accounts under my control [Final Team Agreements email, 9316d57e-4e50-46b8-9ab2-3e374337ff3c].\\n\\u003e 2.  All local system trash, recycle bins, and secondary backups on my hardware have been completely emptied.\\n\\u003e 3.  All temporary application ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n46: \n47: […]         \"text\": \" [019ef48d-8eef-7159-ae9d-2b041e2a0bd9]:\\n\\n1.  **The Trigger:** Sonia\\u0027s interim marketing agreement or a specific project S\"       }, { L6392:         \"text\": \"OW ends (e.g., her work on the Amapiano workshop wraps up)\"       }, {         \"text\": \" [9316d57e-4e50-46b8-9ab2-3e374337ff3c, Final Team Agreements email].\\n2.  **The Delivery:** You (via the AFJ Admin email or your upcoming self\" […]\n48: \n49: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T15:44:51.835Z\"     }, { L7041:       \"text\": \"You are entirely correct. If Sonia has to pay £100 (or even £83.33) in physical cash to cover the VAT, the \\\"services-in-kind\\\" barter is no longer cash-free for her [9316d57e-4e50-46b8-9ab2-3e374337ff3c, 019ef47b-9ecb-7acf-8617-9dc03595964f]. It penalizes her for AFJ’s growth, creates friction, and defeats the spirit of a mutually beneficial, cashless collaboration [9316d57e-4e50-46b8-9ab2-3e374337ff3c].\\n\\nTo preserve the mutual benefit, the three standard methods are used to resolve this:\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Option 1: Stay unregistered for VAT (The primary strategy)\\nThe most practical solution is to **remain unregistered for VAT** [019ef47b-9ecb-7acf-8617-9dc03595964f]. \\n*   **The Key Rule:** Under HMRC guidelines, **public funding grants (like those from the Arts Council of Wales) do not count toward your taxable turnover** [377094b8-0a5e-4915-9e8e-1bffa4923e7a]. \\n*   Only commercial sales (such as ticket sales for workshops and merchandise) count toward the **£90,000 compulsory registration threshold** [019ef47b-9ecb-7acf-8617-9dc03595964f].\\n*   As long as AFJ’s commercial sales remain below £90,000, you do not register. No VAT is charged, no invoices show VAT, and **the barter remains 100% cash-free and mutually beneficial on both sides** [019ef47b-9ecb-7acf-8617-9dc03595964f, 9316d57e-4e50-46b8-9ab2-3e374337ff3c].\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Option 2: Internal VAT Absorption (If AFJ is forced to register)\\nIf AFJ’s commercial sales exceed £90,000 and the company *must* register for VAT, but Plamedi wants to keep the deal mutually beneficial for Sonia [019ef47b-9ecb-7acf-8617-9dc03595964f]:\\n\\n*   **The Setup:** The contract is written so the £500 barter value is **inclusive of VAT** [019ef47b-9ecb-7acf-8617-9dc03595964f].\\n*   **The Invoices:** \\n    *   Sonia (non-VAT registered) invoices AFJ **£500** (no VAT).\\n    *   AFJ (VAT registered) invoices Sonia **£500 (inclusive of £83.33 VAT)** [01... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n50: \n51: […]         \"text\": \":** Under HMRC guidelines, **public funding grants (like those from the Arts Council of Wales) do not count toward your taxable turnover**\"       }, { L7066:         \"text\": \" [377094b8-0a5e-4915-9e8e-1bffa4923e7a]. \\n*   Only commercial sales (such as ticket sales for workshops and merchandise) count toward\"       }, {         \"text\": \" the **Â£90,000 compulsory registration threshold**\" […]\n52: \n53: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T15:53:20.996Z\"     }, { L7674:       \"text\": \"Yes, **this is a very real, rapidly growing field** at the intersection of software engineering and law. It is variously known in the enterprise space as **Legal Engineering**, **Computational Law**, **Policy-as-Code (PaC)**, or **Smart Legal Contracts**.\\n\\nUnder English law and global technical standards, there are established historical precedents, definitions, and open-source frameworks designed to do exactly what you described: mapping a signed, natural-language contract directly to automated system behaviors and event-triggered notifications [6a5b7060-3f47-473b-9a9b-ee6368471805].\\n\\nThe historical precedents, technical frameworks, and concrete ways you can implement this in your **AKCloud/OCI** workspace are detailed below [e8e9804c-a859-4727-9613-f4ff9e7597b8].\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 1. The Historical Precedents\\n\\n#### A. The Ricardian Contract (Ian Grigg, 1996)\\nThe definitive legal and technical precedent for this is the **Ricardian Contract**, invented by financial cryptographer Ian Grigg. \\n*   **What it is:** A Ricardian contract is a single digital document that is simultaneously:\\n    1.  **Read by humans:** (A standard legal contract outlining rights and obligations, such as your DPA or NDA) [Final Team Agreements email].\\n    2.  **Read by software:** (A structured database file, like JSON or XML, containing variables, trigger conditions, and parameters) [714f9cd6-e39a-4f72-a404-eb5bf84be77a].\\n*   It is cryptographically signed by both parties, meaning the software can verify the legal agreement is genuine and automatically execute actions (like triggering payments or blocking access) based on the text.\\n\\n#### B. The Accord Project (Linux Foundation)\\nThe leading modern open-source standard for smart legal contracts is the **Accord Project**, managed under the Linux Foundation.\\n*   They developed a domain-specific programming language called **Ergo** specifically to write e... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n54: \n55: […]         \"text\": \" [019ef48d-8eef-7159-ae9d-2b041e2a0bd9]\\n\\n#### Scenario C: The Public-Facing Storefront Disclaimer Trigger (Consumer Rights Compliance)\\n*   **The Contract Term\"       }, { L7777:         \"text\": \":** Your IT governance policy states that all public-facing payment links (like SumUp or Stripe) must have a legal disclaimer and\"       }, {         \"text\": \" refund consent box before purchase [Accuracy_verification.json, Final Team Agreements email].\\n*   **The Code:** You write a simple\" […]\n56: \n57: […]         \"text\": \" [6a5b7060-3f47-473b-9a9b-ee6368471805].\\n*   **The System\"       }, { L7785:         \"text\": \" Action:** If Dez attempts to deploy a new version of the website to Netlify containing a Stripe payment link that lacks the required `data\"       }, {         \"text\": \"-refund-consent` CSS class, the GitHub Action blocks the build, prevents the deploy, and emails Dez\" […]\n58: \n59: […]         \"text\": \" [6a5b7060-3f47-473b-9a9b-ee6368471805]:\\n    \\u003e *\\\"Deploy Blocked: New payment link detected on page\"       }, { L7791:         \"text\": \" `/merch` lacking Consumer Rights Act 2015 disclaimers, violating IT Governance SOP-02\"       }, {         \"text\": \". Please apply the required disclaimers to proceed.\\\"* [Final Team Agreements email]\\n\\n### Why this is the\" […]\n60: \n61: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T16:19:59.993Z\"     }, { L8263:       \"text\": \"**Clarifying the Query**\\n\\nI\\u0027m now focused on dissecting Andie\\u0027s request. My understanding is that she wants to know if she, specifically, can apply to ACW for her drumming school/practice, even if it\\u0027s structured as a SaaS business. I\\u0027m clarifying the core elements of the inquiry: the applicant (Andie), the project (drumming school/practice), the funding body (ACW), and the business model (SaaS).\\n\\n\\n**Analyzing the Core Ideas**\\n\\nI\\u0027m now zeroing in on the new framing and considering the \\\"after social media ban\\\" premise. It\\u0027s an interesting condition to factor. I\\u0027m assessing if the Arts Council of Wales could be relevant given their creative practice focus, and how this premise might play out in different funding streams. My instinct is that it needs a strong artistic element to qualify, even for a digital platform.\\n\\n\\n**Assessing Fund Suitability**\\n\\nI am now evaluating the suitability of current Arts Council of Wales funds for a digital drumming project. I\\u0027ve pinpointed \\\"Creative Practice/Steps for Individuals\\\" as potentially ideal for Andie, if he\\u0027s seeking to refine his drumming instruction. \\\"Research \\u0026 Development\\\" also seems applicable for a high-quality project. I am considering these avenues for eligibility, which need to be verified.\\n\\n\\n**Framing for Artistic Context**\\n\\nI\\u0027m now focusing on how to position the project within an artistic context, since ACW wouldn\\u0027t fund a purely commercial SaaS venture. The digital platform must serve as a delivery method for an artistic or community engagement project. I\\u0027m considering structuring it around an open-source, private, sovereign digital framework to ensure artistic control and community focus. The main beneficiaries should be those participating in or experiencing the artistic activity.\\n\\n**Refining Project Purpose**\\n\\nI\\u0027m presently zeroing in o... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n62: \n63: […]         \"thought\": true       }, { L8287:         \"text\": \"**Re-framing the Application**\\n\\nI\\u0027ve been drilling into the ACW\\u0027s funding restrictions. It\\u0027s clear that standard music tuition is a no-go. I need to pivot the application\\u0027s framing to emphasize community engagement and workshop development. This shifts the focus from a drumming school to a series of culturally focused workshops, qualifying it as eligible individual creative practice, allowing me to potentially secure the funds.\\n\\n\\n\",         \"thought\": true       }, { […]\n64: \n65: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T16:19:59.996Z\"     }, { L8301:       \"text\": \"Yes, you can absolutely apply to the **Arts Council of Wales (ACW)**, but **you cannot fund it as a standard \\\"drumming school,\\\" \\\"one-to-one lessons,\\\" or a \\\"commercial SaaS\\\" product.** \\n\\nTo get funded, you must navigate two strict exclusions in their guidelines and structure your proposal using specific, eligible frameworks.\\n\\nBased on official, active **Arts Council of Wales (arts.wales)** guidelines and funding documents, here is the exact reality of how to make your project eligible:\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Part 1: The Two Exclusions You Must Avoid\\n\\n#### 1. The \\\"Music Tuition\\\" Exclusion\\nIf you apply to fund a \\\"drumming school\\\" or ongoing weekly lessons, your application will be immediately declined. \\n*   **The Source (ACW *Have a Go* and General Lottery Guidelines):** The official guidelines explicitly list under ineligible activities:\\n    \\u003e *“Music tuition – by this we mean one-to-one, music lessons or ongoing sessions, rather than a workshop or having a go at something new.”*\\n*   **The Workaround:** You must never use the terms \\\"tuition,\\\" \\\"music lessons,\\\" or \\\"school.\\\" Instead, you must frame the activity as a **participatory, community-focused, and non-commercial workshop series** designed to engage underserved communities with rhythm.\\n\\n#### 2. The \\\"Commercial Software\\\" Exclusion\\nACW does not fund commercial businesses or standard Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) products meant for retail sale. \\n*   **The Source (ACW National Lottery Funding Guidelines):** The guidelines state that funding is strictly for the promotion and development of the arts and public engagement, not private commercial software development.\\n*   **The Workaround:** You must not frame the software as a commercial product. You must frame it as **\\\"digital arts infrastructure\\\"** designed to deliver a non-commercial, public-access **cultural preservation project**.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Part 2: The... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n66: \n67: […]         \"text\": \" ineligible activities:\\n    \\u003e *â€œMusic tuition â€“ by this we mean one-to-one, music lessons\"       }, { L8451:         \"text\": \" or ongoing sessions, rather than a workshop or having a go at something new.”*\\n*   **The Workaround:** You must\"       }, {         \"text\": \" never use the terms \\\"tuition,\\\" \\\"music lessons,\\\" or \\\"school.\\\" Instead, you must frame the activity as a **\" […]\n68: \n69: […]         \"text\": \" never use the terms \\\"tuition,\\\" \\\"music lessons,\\\" or \\\"school.\\\" Instead, you must frame the activity as a **\"       }, { L8455:         \"text\": \"participatory, community-focused, and non-commercial workshop series** designed to engage underserved communities with rhythm\"       }, {         \"text\": \".\\n\\n#### 2. The \\\"Commercial Software\\\" Exclusion\\nACW does not fund commercial businesses\" […]\n70: \n71: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T16:27:24.440Z\"     }, { L9008:       \"text\": \"Creative Practice (Individuals): Up to £10,000 [1.1.3].\\nThe Match: This is a development grant designed to give you time and space to experiment and learn. It has no strict match-funding requirement.\\n\\nand this can cover me creating drumming material which i then put on my site ? and share with the broader usw and for families with kids and whatnot??\",       \"role\": \"user\",       \"tokenCount\": 83, […]\n72: \n73: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T16:33:50.250Z\"     }, { L9148:       \"text\": \"Yes, **the grant can cover purchasing a drum kit to keep at home, but under strict rules, a spending cap, and a specific legal justification.** [1.2.2]\\n\\nThe Arts Council of Wales (ACW) will not fund equipment simply for personal recreation or casual practice [1.2.2]. However, under the **Creative Practice** individual grant, you are permitted to purchase the physical tools of your trade if they are essential to deliver the project [1.1.3, 1.2.2].\\n\\nHere are the strict guidelines and the exact way you must structure and justify this purchase in your application [1.2.2]:\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 1. The Financial Limit on Equipment\\n\\nIn individual revenue grants (like the £10,000 *Creative Practice* scheme), there is a strict limit on capital equipment purchases [1.1.3, 1.2.2]:\\n*   **The Cap:** ACW typically caps equipment and materials at **£2,000.00** of the total project budget [1.2.2]. \\n*   This means you can easily allocate **£1,500.00 to £2,000.00** of your £10,000 grant to buy a high-quality drum kit, but the remaining £8,000.00 must be spent on your time (fees), mentoring, or other project-delivery costs [1.1.3, 1.2.2].\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. The Smart Choice: An Electronic/Silent Drum Kit\\n\\nSince you want to rehearse \\\"at the comfort of your home\\\" without disrupting your family or neighbors (recalling your May 29 conversation about parents wanting \\\"peace and quiet\\\" and using \\\"silent drums\\\") [29/05/2026, 15:09:32, 29/05/2026, 15:09:51], your ideal purchase is a **high-end electronic drum kit** (such as a *Roland V-Drums* setup) [29/05/2026, 15:09:51]. \\n\\nAn electronic kit is significantly easier to justify to the Arts Council than an acoustic kit because of its technical utility [1.2.2].\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. How You Must Justify the Purchase in the Bid\\n\\nDo not write: *\\\"I want a grant to buy a drum kit so I can practice jazz at home.\\\"* That will be immediately rejected as a personal ho... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n74: \n75: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T17:10:25.465Z\"     }, { L11019:       \"text\": \"**Analyzing Copyright Concerns**\\n\\nI\\u0027m currently focused on identifying any instances where \\\"she\\\" (Plamedi) expressed concerns about soundtrack copyright within the provided chat logs. I\\u0027m carefully reviewing the text to pinpoint any direct references or indirect implications of worry about legal or ethical issues regarding the use of music. My primary goal is to isolate and document any such expressions accurately.\\n\\n\\n**Investigating Media Questions**\\n\\nI\\u0027m now investigating potential media-related concerns within the logs. I\\u0027m focusing on \\\"video,\\\" \\\"music,\\\" and related terms, checking for any expressions of worry or uncertainty. I\\u0027m noting specific dates and times, looking for conversations that hint at ethical or legal considerations. I\\u0027ve found an initial discussion related to a dance shoot and accessibility concerns, which prompted a re-evaluation, so I am expanding my search to related keywords in that time-frame.\\n\\n\\n**Examining Music Timing**\\n\\nI\\u0027m now investigating concerns about music synchronization in the logs. I see discussion about a song being \\\"off\\\" and a video being \\\"a split second late,\\\" with Plamedi downplaying it. This prompts further examination of timing concerns. It appears Plamedi is willing to edit the audio, and Sonia thinks it will work on Instagram.\\n\\n\\n**Considering Video Quality Issues**\\n\\nI\\u0027m now investigating potential video quality concerns and related issues, prompted by Plamedi\\u0027s comment about quality decreases on Instagram and its impact on promotional videos. I\\u0027m focusing on \\\"quality,\\\" \\\"insta,\\\" and \\\"promo,\\\" as well as \\\"delete\\\" and \\\"amend\\\". I\\u0027m specifically searching for instances where a video might have been altered or removed due to music-related or alignment issues. I\\u0027m recalling the previous search terms and re-evaluating the chat logs, now expanding the searc... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n76: \n77: […]         \"thought\": true       }, { L11039:         \"text\": \"**Assessing Legal Compliance**\\n\\nI\\u0027m now investigating potential legal compliance issues, moving from copyright to broader consumer rights concerns, as prompted by Andie\\u0027s email referencing the Consumer Rights Act. I see discussions about workshop delays and their impact on promotional materials. There\\u0027s concern about low sales, linked to delays, and I\\u0027m noting the need to formalize agreements with David. I\\u0027m focusing on the dates and actions around the Fathom meeting summary from June 5, 2026.\\n\\n\\n\",         \"thought\": true       }, { […]\n78: \n79: […]       \"createTime\": \"2026-06-23T17:16:12.347Z\"     }, { L11410:       \"text\": \"Scanning Plamedi’s actual social media footprint across her active platforms—**Instagram (`@afj_cardiff`), YouTube (`@afjcardiff`), and TikTok (`@afjcardiff`)**—reveals that **she has almost certainly been experiencing algorithmic reach suppression (shadowbanning) and structural limitations for some time.**\\n\\nHer real-world impact is massive: she has been featured on **ITV Wales**, is recognized as Wales\\u0027s first dedicated Afro-Dance organization, and hosts highly popular, energetic physical classes. Yet, her digital footprint does not match this real-world scale. \\n\\nHere is the objective analysis of her platforms and the evidence of algorithmic suppression:\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 1. YouTube (`@afjcardiff`) — The Organic Visibility Ceiling\\n*   **The Metrics:** Her YouTube channel has **374 subscribers** and **60 videos**. \\n*   **The View Pattern:** Her videos show a classic \\\"suppression ceiling\\\":\\n    *   Her highly polished workshop videos (like the *Afrofusion Collaboration with Johnny* or *Ndombolo meets Coupé Décalé*) are capped at **1.2k to 1.5k views**.\\n    *   Her standard, highly valuable class reviews and tutorials (like the *Loketo/Ndombolo step tutorials*) drop instantly to **100 to 200 views**.\\n*   **The Cause:** YouTube\\u0027s Content ID and copyright-matching engines are exceptionally strict. Because her class videos utilize commercial Afrobeat tracks in the background, her organic reach is suppressed. The algorithm restricts these videos to her existing subscribers and direct searchers, preventing them from being recommended on global homepages.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. Instagram (`@afj_cardiff`) — The Commercial Muting Risk\\nAs shown throughout your April to June 2026 WhatsApp exchanges, Plamedi and Sonia are highly active on Instagram but rely entirely on commercial tracks (e.g., Davido, Chris Brown, Uncle Waffles) to promote workshops and classes.\\n*   **The Problem:** Be... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n80: \n\n(Showing lines 1-80 of 165. Use offset=81 to continue.)\n</content>",
