      "output": "=== Merch/Stripe/cart snippets in Nostalgia D'Italia portal (2_11AM, 1.7MB) ===\nL642:  Welcome to the technical handover and design briefing portal. This interactive \"Bacheca\" or bulletin board serves as the baseline for our meeting with Joanne on 2 June 2026. The goal is to move Nostalgia D'Italia from a\nL646:  andiekobbietech Solutions acts as the Technical Product Manager and Lead Business Analyst on this project. Our role is to build out the transactional back-end infrastructure, optimise cold-chain logistics, enforce intel\nL665:  One of the most emotional parts of that trip was spending time with my Italian grandmother, Mamma Vera. I have returned to Italy many times throughout my life and spent time with La Nanna countless times before, but thi\nL666:  What stayed with me was not only the products themselves, but what they represented. Every jar, every package, every small item carried memory, affection, heritage, and identity. It felt like culture and tradition being\nL667:  That trip became the emotional foundation for Nostalgia D'Italia. Nostalgia D'Italia is more than a business, podcast, or creative project - it is a deeply personal story about identity, migration, heritage, and the emo\nL668:  At its core, Nostalgia D'Italia is about heritage and community. It celebrates Italian culture not only through products and cuisine, but through memory, family, migration, identity, and shared human experiences. It als\nL676:  Joanne (Jo) West has been selected as the Creative and Communications Lead on this project because of her exceptional background in managing complex graphic campaigns, communication channels, and video-editing pipelines\nL729:  Given the customer has items in their cart totalling \"&pound;55.00\" \nL751:  ADR-001: Mobile Web Cataloguing with WhatsApp Checkout Integration \nL761:  Jemima's customer base has grown organically in the Midlands through local events and word-of-mouth. As seen in the Nostalgica Supermarket poster (Figure 09), the primary transaction flow relies on direct WhatsApp engag\nL765:  We will build a high-fidelity, mobile-optimised web catalogue showing real-time inventory, integrated directly with a WhatsApp Checkout routing API. When a customer adds items (such as Mulino Bianco biscuits, CIRIO toma\nL769:  This architecture eliminates complex merchant gateway integrations, keeping platform costs low. Joanne must design mobile web interfaces and promotional assets that explicitly highlight this WhatsApp-led checkout pipeli\nL795:  This provides 100% legal ownership over the brand's visual identity, rendering them safe for registration with the Intellectual Property Office (IPO) and preparation for the investor \"Data Room\" . No generative AI files\nL873:  A core product offering is fresh, authentic Italian groceries and cured meats (e.g., Levoni Coppa Stagionata, cheeses). Shipping perishable, temperature-sensitive food nationwide through typical logistics channels runs \nL880:  Perishables (charcuterie, cheeses) will be isolated during checkout, triggering a mandatory cold-chain insulated packaging fee of �4.99 and restricting delivery options to Next-Day Thermal Express. \n\n=== H1/H2/H3 in Nostalgia D'Italia 2_11AM ===\n  [1] Nostalgia D'Italia\n  [2] Professionalising Nostalgia D'Italia's Brand & Digital Systems Architecture\n  [3] The Handoff Architecture\n  [3] Jemima's Journey �?\" Udine to the West Midlands\n  [3] The Joanne West Brief �?\" Professionalising AI Concepts\n  [3] Gherkin System Requirements\n  [3] Architecture Decision Records (ADRs)\n  [3] Nostalgia D'Italia Visual Portfolio\n  [3] Brand & Technical Glossary\n  [3] Google Meet Handover Agenda\n  [3] Bacheca Live Notes\n",
