      "output": "=== AFJ_Meeting_June12_2026.md (size 4 KB) ===\n# AFJ Cardiff Weekly Meeting - June 12, 2026\n\n**Recording:** [Fathom Video (181 mins)](https://fathom.video/share/f9vAsGxGBiznqCKqzk61rkkp2fzMEFS4)\n\n**Participants:** Sonia, Andrea P Enning (Andy), Plamedi (mentioned)\n\n---\n\n## Key Topics\n\n### 1. Funding Application (Arts Council Wales)\n- Application submitted, awaiting response by ~July\n- Budget estimated at **�10K-15K** total\n- Videographer quoted **�3K-3.5K** for filming + editing\n- Contingency plan if funding fails - scale down but don't scrap the idea\n- Other funding sources being explored simultaneously (Create, International Fund)\n\n### 2. Project: \"Afro Dancers Narratives\"\n- **Core concept:** Afro dance is cultural memory and storytelling\n- **Purpose:** \n  - Show Afro dance is more than a trend (beyond TikTok/social media)\n  - Create an education/reference tool for understanding Afro dance\n  - Draw a clear line between cultural appreciation and cultural appropriation\n- **Format:** Documentary film + workshop series + community discussions + panel\n- **Timeline:** \n  - July: Contracts in place, research & conversations\n  - Aug-Sep: Filming, creative exploration, movement workshops\n  - October (Black History Month): Community engagement, anniversary event, screening\n  - November: Reflection, evaluation, project documentation\n\n### 3. Documentary Details\n- **Interviewees:**\n  - Dance teachers (Homebros focus): How they preserve culture, creative process\n  - Elders/older generation: Different migration experience, community building\n  - Younger generation (18-20): Current experience in Wales\n  - Panel discussion at screening event\n- **Duration:** TBD - possibly 30 min or multi-episode series\n- **Producer:** Onismo (Urban Stamp) - sent full proposal, mood book, pricing deck\n  - 7+ years experience, part of Urban Circle (20 years)\n  - Highly recommended - proactive, organized, included contingency in pricing\n\n### 4. Logistics\n- **Venues:** National Dance Company Wales (but only 1 day available), possibly Newport\n- **Anniversary:** October during Black History Month\n- **Screening event:** Film + panel discussion + possible performance\n- **AFJ Classroom:** Online educational platform being built (membership model)\n- **Storyboarding session:** Planned with Onismo (end of June/July)\n\n### 5. Cultural Themes Discussed\n- Cultural appreciation vs appropriation (e.g., the \"Kukere\" vs \"Itziki\" name correction)\n- Gentrification of London (Peckham example) and its effect on multicultural spaces\n- Different migrant generation experiences (elders who stuck together vs younger generation thrown into Welsh culture)\n- Afro-Welsh identity emerging (Black Welsh content creators speaking Welsh)\n- Red Bull's role in promoting Afro dance globally\n- Azonto's 2012 explosion in the UK - Fuse ODG's role in globalizing it\n- Beyonc�'s \"Run the World\" Ethiopian dancer controversy (credit delayed)\n- Colorism within the community (brother's experience being told he was \"too dark\")\n- The Polish Afro dancer controversy - should culture be shared openly or protected?\n\n### 6. Action Items\n- [ ] Share Miro mind map access with Andy\n- [ ] Create Trello board from today's discussion\n- [ ] Plan storyboarding session with Onismo (end of June/July)\n- [ ] Explore International Fund and Create funding applications simultaneously\n- [ ] Research elders/community spaces for interviews\n- [ ] Build AFJ Classroom website before documentary launch\n- [ ] Andy to share ethnography research framework (Clearview methodology)\n- [ ] Sonia to clean up and consolidate Miro mind map\n\n### 7. Other Opportunities Mentioned\n- **Art Council Wales Edinburgh trip:** Funding for creatives to network in Edinburgh (applications close June 16)\n- **Startup Studio seminar series:** Production management in arts (Gary Clark, Newport-based)\n- **International Fund:** Separate from current application - for taking work back to Africa\n- **Create fund:** For research & development \u001a event/show production\n- **Sona (edtech):** Platform by Fuse ODG teaching African culture/history\n- **Afro Dictionary:** Reference platform for Afro dance terms and concepts\n\n",
